🤍WHAT A YEAR🤍 
This year included decorating and then leaving a home, a significant breakup, a new incredible job, leaving Chicago after almost 9 years, trying Charleston on for size, the loss of two family members, tons of travel and so much more. I’m here to remind you that when one door closes, a whole universe opens. And I promise you will be happier for it❤️‍🔥 

As I reflect on 2022 I wanted to share the top lessons I learned each month from the craziest year of my life. Hope it helps 
✨ January: trust your instincts
✨ February: it’s ok to change your mind
✨March: you can do hard things
✨April: new beginnings are a gift
✨May: nothing is more important than family
✨June: biscuits are delicious 
✨July: love is more important than milestones
✨August: nothing rejuvenates like a girls’s trip
✨September: don’t give up
✨October: age is just a number and getting older is a privilege 
✨November: there are incredible communities of humans out there you have yet to meet. 
✨December: taking life into your own hands is incredibly empowering. 

Happy NYE friends !

I tried a Keratin Express and here’s how it went…

I recently went to see Jay at Stella Nova to combat what I’ve been considering my “Southern Hair” aka the fluffiest (read frizziest) my hair has ever been.

I am no stranger to frizz- I’ve always dealt with it but the humidity in Charleston is a different beast. My beauty routines must always have one necessary feature- be low maintenance. So I decided to try out the Keratin Express to give me glorious locks on the go especially with the amount I travel. 

So what is it?
A Keratin Express treatment leaves your hair frizz free and smooth by using keratin, which is a protein found in your hair, to smooth out your strands. 

Why?
It manages frizz, adds shine, and cuts drying time in half. It’s been a game changer for my hair especially when I let it air dry. It looks SO good. 

Keratin Express vs Regular Keratin?
Last time I got a Keratin was in 2018 and the girl who did it FRIED my hair. Not only was it damaged but it was so flat. Jay and I decided to go with the Keratin Express to dip my toe back into the treatment pool after my scarring experience allowing me to see if I like the look. Keratin Express takes 1.5- 2hrs instead of 2-4 hours. It lasts 1-2 months depending on how well you care for it vs the 4-5 months of a regular Keratin treatment so it is less of a commitment. I also like my curls so the express is better for removing the frizz without making the hair much straighter. 

My take on it? I’m pretty much in love- it has been a GAME-CHANGER. If you decide to try it, make sure to ask around for an expert!

Greetings from (when I was in) Panamá 🧚. Which should go on the postcard?
It ain’t easy being green 💚
Orange you glad I didn’t say banana? 🍊

A few weeks ago the women in my family and I went on a trip to Mexico to celebrate my Aunt Di’s birthday. We traveled from 5 different states. 

The only way to describe this trip is simply “fabulous.” Traveling to San Miguel de Allende was a first for all of us which meant catching that hint of wonder and adventure in everyone’s eye. At dinner each night we made a point to have some intentional conversation. We laughed, cried some happy tears, and then laughed. And laughed. And laughed. We all looked around in amazement and discussed how lucky we were to have a family of women who love each other so much and are constantly there to supply support. We compared ourselves to the Ya Ya Sisterhood. It was the first time I looked around and saw this group as best friends rather than the respective roles they play within the family dynamic. 

In honor of International Women’s Day I wanted to share this because rather than compare and contrast with other women, we should be using the energy to cherish the women in our lives that matter. Whether or not you have sisters or strong female bonds in your family, you have the ability to build your own tribe. Remember this next time you find your mind slipping to an unproductive place: All tides rise together and There is room for everyone at the table. Oh yea- and f the patriarchy 😜 Ya Ya!!!!

Girls weekend ✔️

This weekend 3 of my girlfriends flew down the shore from Chicago and it was so much fun. It’s interesting making friends as an adult. People say it’s hard but I find it so enriching. You really get to choose your people. 

I always knew I loved my friends but I never realized how truly amazing they are until last year when I really needed them. Going through a massive breakup, figuring out what the f was next for me and they were each there to pick me up, pack me up and light me up in their own ways. My advice to finding your people? Vulnerability. Let people see the real you. Speak your truth. Talk about what you’re dealing with. Connection is important. It allows others to feel comfortable around you. You’ll be surprised how many people can relate and you never know who your story will help. Xx

12.31.23 and prior 🌙

I planned on ‘23 being the year I took control of my life. I really took a go at it. I cried a ton and felt lost 75% of the time but that’s cool. Here are the biggest highlights that I feel comfortable sharing
- visited 4 countries
- made new amazing friends
- stopped talking to some people
- left a job
- relaunched my company
- got my real estate license 
- questioned the meaning of life
- had a Friday the 13th birthday
- watched the scariest war of my lifetime (IMO) unfold 

All this to say, hoping for mental sanity in 2024. ⭐️
